title.narrative: HPN- Cross Border Health Integrated Partnership Project (CB-HIPP)

description.narrative: (USAID East Africa Regional): CB-HIPP is a regional Leader with Associates (LWA) Cooperative Agreement. With FY 2016 investments in the CB-HIPP mechanism, USAID will support sustainable African-led health sector development to improve health outcomes among mobile populations and vulnerable communities residing along eastern Africa's cross-border areas and transport corridors. CB-HIPP will continue its work with the East Africa Community (EAC) to implement a standard package of services tailored to the region's mobile and vulnerable cross-border populations; design health insurance products; and formulate relevant policies that are supportive to these populations. CB-HIPP service delivery sites include land border areas along major transport corridors and wet border areas along East Africa's major lakes, including Lake Victoria, Lake Kivu, and Lake Tanganyika..
